</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/16/01 8:52:09 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Question about Raid costs</span><hr size=1> I'm part of a discussion on another board and as a point of reference would like to ask some of you much more experinced Raid leader types about the average cost of some basic raids.<br>
<br>
As i understand it most costs cover cleric/enchanter buffs, any port stones needed and in the worst case, a bad CR. <br>
<br>
what i'm wondering is are there any other 'costs' of running a raid (pp wise not the extreame stress cost <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and how do you as a guild/raid leader/raid goer/buffer offset these costs so as not to drain your own bank while having fun with friends. The main raids i'm looking at are the basic ones FGs Vox/Naggy hate/fear type, what i see as the lower lvl ones. Any and all info is greatly appriciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueoralsolis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EoralSolis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/16/01 9:36:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about Raid costs</span><hr size=1> Typically I loose money on Vox, Naggy, Fear and Sky, and I make money on Hate.  Hate raids basically finance all our other activities, though I have taken up guild collections when sugar daddy Eoral starts seeing the moths come out of hs coin purse.  I typically spend the following:<br>
<br>
FGs--Jacinths only, Maybe 3-5 stacks including rune, 100 pp total cost.<br>
<br>
Vox/Naggy--40 Pearls &amp; 80 Peris for a 36 person crew, for Death Pact, Natron/Marzin and Rune IV for everyone.  1100 pp total cost.<br>
<br>
Fear--40 Pearls 120 Peris 100 Jacinths, Death Pact and Natron/Marzin for pull, Pinzarn for camp, Chain Rune as needed.  42 person crew.  Damn those TT Glare Lords and Jellow Cubes for your dispells!  1500 pp total cost.<br>
<br>
Hate--80 Pearls, 200 Peris 10 Port stones.  No Pinzarn, Rune for Mini Bosses and to save chanters/clerics/puller, Natron and Death Pact used liberaly, including full crew for portal break.  42 person raid crew for both floors.  6100 pp total cost.<br>
<br>
Sky--80 pearls 200 peris 12 port stones plus a 5k reserve for coffins, 24-36 person raid crew.  No Pinzarn, Rune for Isle 3 and Bosses and to save chanters/clerics/puller, Natron and Death Pact used liberaly.  6500 pp total cost not counting 5k coffin reserve fund.  (you can buy coffins on isle one)<br>
<br>
That is pretty much the reason why I take all cash items.<br>
<br>
Eoral Solis<br>
Servant of Evoluxa <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uninadene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ninadene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/16/01 11:46:02 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about Raid costs</span><hr size=1> just for the sake of arguement.... would you ever expect/ask someone to attend your raid and buff/port/summon the crew out of their own pocket?<br>
<br>
and what if any would be the reason you attended a raid that expected/asked that of you? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphazy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phazy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/16/01 12:14:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about Raid costs</span><hr size=1> alot of lower level guilds ask for 300-1k to attend a PoA raid (least they use to ..been about 4 months since i looked at a poa signup).<br>
<br>
<br>
I went on ONE raid that announced they wouldnt be reimbursing reagents ..and soem people in the guild who didnt know ..started a stink in guildchat and eventually the raidleader agreed to repayment.<br>
<br>
Alot of raids I am on, its on the reimburse system..you use your reagents ..then after raid is over (and they have colected the loot for raid) they repay you.<br>
<br>
I know ALOT of people who Donate to the raid their Reagents/summons.<br>
<br>
2 people in particular come to mind from my experiences<br>
Argonot on a few occasions I beleive (and one i am certain of) has Convienently forgotten to ask for repayment.<br>
Dymunq on the Drunks Fear raid refused my attempt to repay him for the couple coffins he used to help us speed up on terror cr.<br>
<br>
In general, I think if you want people to come and help by Buffin/summoning, you better darn well expect to repay them if you are leading the raid. Yes times will come when people will refuse the repayment...but you will find it hard to field a raid if word gets out you are not repaying people<br>
<br>
<br>
and IF a raid stated that upfront I would thing only those guaranteed something on the raid ...or we're a close friend to someone getting something on raid and went to help them. <p><center>Phazy Daayz 52st lvl Disciple<center><br><center>Drunks of Tunare..least till they throw me outa the bar<center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>&#60;Silent Redemption&#62;</font></span><br>  Posts: 1631<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/17/01 1:04:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about Raid costs</span><hr size=1> I believe Eoral means Jaspers not Jacinths.  Otherwise is costs are pretty close to what you should plan on.  While you spend alot more on Hate raids you will get alot more back in the way of gems and cash loots. <p><A HREF="http://www.silentredemption.org/" TARGET="_new">
